The course will introduce the concepts of informal logic, including types of arguments and common fallacies of argumentation.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The main general objectives of the course are: 1) to familiarize students with the concepts and ideas of argumentation theory (informal logic) 2) to develop the skills of identifying, analyzing and evaluating arguments 3) to develop the ability to recognize common fallacies in argumentation.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon successful completion of the course the student should: 1) be familiar with some main concepts and topics in informal logic; 2) recognize common fallacies of argumentation; 3) be able to categorize, analyze, evaluate and improve arguments, using the concepts and techniques of informal logic.
